<p>MYRIGHT INC. ("MyRight", "our", "us", or "we") is that Delaware Corporation that hosts, maintains, and moderates www.myright.me ("Website"). </p>

<p>The privacy of your personal information is very important to us. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect your information, what information we collect, how we use it, how we protect the information, and any third-party vendors. User data is collected and managed according to the following Privacy Policy. Please read this before using the Website. By accessing or using the Website, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. </p>

<p>1. How We Collect Your Information</p>

<p>a. When you browse or use our Website, we collect certain information, as explained in the following section.</p>

<p>b. We collect information when you register to join myRight by logging into an account that you already have with certain third-party social networking sites ("SNS") (including, but not limited to, Facebook) via our Service. For example, our Website allows you to create an account and login to the Website using your Facebook account credentials through Facebook Connect. If you are not currently registered as a User on the Website and you click on "Sign in Using Facebook," you will first be asked to enter your Facebook credentials and then be given the option to register and join myRight.</p>

<p>2. Information We Collect and How We Use It</p>

<p>a. Anonymous Data. We collect anonymous data from every visitor of the Website to monitor traffic, fix bugs, and improve the Website. For example we may collect, without limitation, your unique Internet protocol address, the name of your unique Internet service provider, the city, state, and country from which you access our website, the kind of browser or computer you use, the number of clicks within the site, the date and time of your visit, the web page from which you arrived to our site, the pages you viewed on the site, or the time you spent using any portion of the site ("Anonymous Data"). We currently do not utilize cookies for tracking or other purposes. </p>

<p>b. Personal Information. When you decide to create your user account by logging into a SNS via the Website, you are using personal information you have already provided to the SNS such as your "real" name, email address, and other information you make publicly available via the SNS ("Personal Information") to create your user account on our Website; the information we collect may depend on the privacy settings you have with the SNS, so please consult the SNS's privacy and data practices. For example, by using Facebook Connect, you are allowing myRight to access the Personal Information in your Facebook account pursuant to the Facebook Terms of Use regarding your use of the Website via Facebook.    We use your Personal Information (in some cases, in conjunction with your Anonymous Data) to provide the Website services to you. For example:</p>

<p>i. Account registration. We create your user account for your use of the Website based upon the Personal Information you provide. ii. Communications. We use your Personal Information to contact you with myRight newsletters, marketing, or promotional materials and other information that may be of interest to you. If you decide at any time that you no longer wish to receive such communications from us, please follow the unsubscribe instructions provided in any of the communications . iii. Customer service. We use your personal information to respond to your questions and/or inquiries.</p>

<p>3. How we Protect Information</p>

<p>We diligently guard your information and are responsible under state and federal law to facilitate the dissemination of your information and control its viewership. We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information when you use the Website. However, we cannot guarantee that unauthorized persons will never be able to defeat our security measures. </p>

<p> 4. Third Party Use</p>

<p>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer to third parties your personally identifiable information. We understand that legal matters may be deeply personal and respect your privacy. Aggregated and anonymized data is periodically transmitted to third-party vendors to help us improve your experience using the Application. We currently use Google Analytics. </p>

<p>We also use social buttons provided by services such as Twitter, Google+, LinkedIn and Facebook. Your use of these third party services is entirely optional. </p>

<p>5. Links to Other Sites and Services</p>

<p>Our website contains links to other third-party websites and online services. If you choose to visit another website or online service by clicking on a link, you will be direct to that third party's websites or online service. The fact that we may link to a website or online service is not an endorsement, authorization, or representation of our affiliation with that third party, nor is it an endorsement of their privacy or information security policies or practices. We do not exercise control over third party websites and online services, and these third parties may place their own cookies or other files on your computer and collect data or solicit Personal Information and Anonymous Data from you. Other sites and online services follow different rules regarding the collection, use and/or disclosure of Personal Information and Anonymous Data. We are not responsible for the privacy policies and/or practices of these third party services, and you are responsible for reading and understanding those third party services' privacy policies. </p>

<p>6. Changes to Privacy Policy</p>

<p>We may amend this Privacy Policy at any time. Please check back to this page frequently. If we make any changes in the way we collect or use information, we will notify you here, and/or update the Privacy Policy modification date below. By accessing or using the Website after publication of any changes to the Privacy Policy, you agree to be legally bound by such changes.</p>

